:7:"1318524";s:12:"chat_room_id";s:1:"1";s:7:"user_id";s:2:"37";s:6:"handle";s:5:"Augur";s:12:"character_id";s:4:"1139";s:17:"recipient_user_id";N;s:18:"recipient_username";s:3:"Nay";s:4:"text";s:36:"I was curious if you&#039;d like in?";s:9:"timestamp";s:10:"1428373459";s:15:"chat_name_color";s:7:"#9663ff";s:9:"chat_rand";s:11:"14283734590";s:15:"chat_text_color";s:7:"#465cfe";s:16:"chat_log_type_id";s:1:"2";s:6:"viewed";N;}i:1318526;a:14:{s:11:"chat_log_id";s:7:"1318526";s:12:"chat_room_id";s:1:"1";s:7:"user_id";s:5:"11635";s:6:"handle";s:3:"Nay";s:12:"character_id";s:4:"1274";s:17:"recipient_user_id";N;s:18:"recipient_username";s:5:"Augur";s:4:"text";s:40:"Sure~ I would be happy to be of service.";s:9:"timestamp";s:10:"1428373515";s:15:"chat_name_color";s:7:"#e6cc77";s:9:"chat_rand";s:11:"14283771167";s:15:"chat_text_color";s:7:"#b39530";s:16:"chat_log_type_id";s:1:"2";s:6:"viewed";N;}i:1318530;a:14:{s:11:"chat_log_id";s:7:"1318530";s:12:"chat_room_id";s:1:"1";s:7:"user_id";s:2:"37";s:6:"handle";s:5:"Augur";s:12:"character_id";s:4:"1139";s:17:"recipient_user_id";N;s:18:"recipient_username";s:3:"Nay";s:4:"text";s:1466:"Well, it&#039;s in a simple form now, just a basic setting. The idea of having a setting like that is to create a place where high adventures could exist while still being very much pony fitting. We&#039;ve seen in the show that they have their own fictional settings from their books/comics and the like. Well, the plan was to have a setting where all those fictional universes inside the show would bleed together, creating an anaglam world for the characters. For simplicity, I&#039;d compare it to League of Extraordinary Gentleman, the Fable&#039;s series, or DC Comic&#039;s Infinite Crisis. The characters are all being entered into this world by a process called &#039;The Bleed&#039; where, as imagined, their universes bleed into one with the other ones. This would allow for the big events that were promised with Unrest, yet be able to restrict things for a person&#039;s personal event. Though the world would be an anaglam, parts of it would favor genres, to give a distinct theme to that place in the world. There&#039;d be old style victorian townships for the most trying of Van Helsing / Lovecraftian horror and suspense, a prospering metropolis for super powered shenanigans, a great sea for the golden age of saltiness, and a stalwart castle for knightly heroics. &#039;The Bleed&#039; would also account for keeping these characters it equal with each others universes, as if you stray too far from your own settings, your character would adapt.";s:9:"timestamp";s:10:"1428373634";s:15:"chat_name_color";s:7:"#9663ff";s:9:"chat_rand";s:11:"14283736335";s:15:"chat_text_color";s:7:"#465cfe";s:16:"chat_log_type_id";s:1:"2";s:6:"viewed";N;}i:1318534;a:14:{s:11:"chat_log_id";s:7:"1318534";s:12:"chat_room_id";s:1:"1";s:7:"user_id";s:2:"37";s:6:"handle";s:5:"Augur";s:12:"character_id";s:4:"1139";s:17:"recipient_user_id";N;s:18:"recipient_username";s:3:"Nay";s:4:"text";s:876:"the idea has had no dislikes as of yet, and it certainly fits all the spots the site wanted from a high adventure universe. The problem would be managment. There&#039;d have to be specific content supervisors for just that world alone. Those who could help keep players from being overpowered and on level with each other. &#039;Librarians&#039; for the sake of kinship to the setting. They&#039;d be the ones approving characters and ideas for events, yet still fall under the rules of the site and moderation by the Guides. Sapphire would be my first choice of a Guide to overview it all. She has the most experience of the guide team out of making non-pony things pony. Librarians would only exist for content approval for the universe, and help keep things equal by assisting with the Bleed and it&#039;s changes on each thing that does appear or decide to cross settings.";s:9:"timestamp";s:10:"1428373657";s:15:"chat_name_color";s:7:"#9663ff";s:9:"chat_rand";